  "text": "The foregoing results suggested that the M 5 receptor is involved in TASK channel inhibition and that it is mainly located at the extrasynaptic site. This notion was immunocytochemically examined in isolated AM cells. PSD93-like immunoreactive materials, a protein which is a major scaffolding protein at the postsynaptic membrane in sympathetic ganglion cells [CITATION_1] , were detected in about 20% of the surface membrane, whereas M 5 -like IRs were found in about 50% of that (Fig. 7) . These immunocytochemical stainings clearly indicated that the majority of M 5 receptors are present at extrasynaptic sites.",
